    <div class="hero-inner">
      <div>
        <div class="hero-rule"></div>
        <div class="hero-eyebrow">A clinician&apos;s story through the operating model</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">The patients<br>he <em>cannot see</em><br>stay in surveillance.</h1>
        <p class="hero-strap">Adam is a consultant urologist running a PSA Active Surveillance cohort at a large acute trust. He sees his patients on a quarterly cycle. Some miss appointments because of work, travel or caring responsibilities. Some drop out of surveillance entirely. The drop-outs are the patients he worries about most. <strong>This is the story of how the model lets him keep more patients in surveillance without his clinic growing.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-portrait-box">
        <div class="hero-portrait-circ">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/adam.png" alt="Adam">
        </div>
        <div class="hero-portrait-name">Adam</div>
        <div class="hero-portrait-role">Consultant urologist<br>PSA Active Surveillance</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- RIBBON -->
  <div class="ribbon-wrap">
    <div class="ribbon-eyebrow">Adam&apos;s journey at a glance &middot; six stages, one cohort</div>
    <div class="ribbon">
      <a class="ribbon-stage" href="#stage-1">
        <div class="ribbon-num">1</div>
        <div class="ribbon-label">The cohort</div>
        <div class="ribbon-substage">The patients in front of him</div>
      </a>
      <a class="ribbon-stage" href="#stage-2">
        <div class="ribbon-num">2</div>
