        <div class="stage-eyebrow">First home prescriptions &middot; right patient, right cycle</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">Adam picks the first patients carefully. Stable surveillance trajectory. Comfortable with the kit. Comfortable with the clinical safety net behind it. Mark is one of the first. The kit goes home, the result comes back, the next clinic does not. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="adam-s4"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Adam Story/adam-stage4.png" alt="Adam Stage 4" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">I am picking patients I would already trust with their own monitoring if the tooling existed. Stable trend, comfortable with the kit, family at home who can help if needed. The model meets them where they already are.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Adam</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What this looks like in clinic</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">A short conversation at the end of the in-clinic appointment: would you be comfortable doing the next blood at home? Almost every patient says yes. The kit ships from the supplier. The patient takes the sample on the date the clinic would have happened. The lab processes it. The result lands in Adam&apos;s system before he would have seen the patient. <strong>The clinic visit that did not happen is one he did not have capacity for anyway.</strong></div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old shape</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Every patient comes in every quarter. No tier of patients reading their trend remotely. No clinic time freed for the patients whose disease behaviour means clinic is the right venue. The clinic-only model treats every patient as if they need clinic time, regardless of whether they clinically do.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">Who is operating the pathway</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">The clinical nurse specialist coordinating onboarding. The supplier shipping the kit. The lab processing the sample. The platform delivering the result back. The patient.</div>
          </div>
